<div class="cover">
  <h1 class="cover-heading">
    Instant iCal feeds for your EVE Online calendar.
  </h1>

  <section class="cover-feature">
    <h4 class="mb-5">What you can do with <%= site_name %>?</h4>
    <div class="card-deck">
      <div class="card border-0">
        <%= image_tag "devices.png", class: "mx-auto d-block w-25" %>
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title font-weight-light">Use your calendar app</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-0">
        <%= image_tag "time-zones.png", class: "mx-auto d-block w-25" %>
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title font-weight-light">See events in your time zone</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-0">
        <%= image_tag "sharing.png", class: "mx-auto d-block w-25" %>
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title font-weight-light">Keep everyone in the loop</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cover-feature">
    <h4>Convenient out-of-game access</h4>
    <p>Use your favourite calendar app on the desktop or mobile. Outlook, Apple Calendar,
    Google Calendar, or phone's native - you choose.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cover-feature">
    <h4>Your time zone</h4>
    <p>Choose the time zone event time is shown in. No more missed events!</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cover-feature">
    <h4>Keep everyone in the loop</h4>
    <p>Having a single location for scheduled incursion runs, mining operations,
    or the occasional roam keeps everyone on the same page.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cover-feature">
    <h4>You're always in control</h4>
    <p>You decide who to share with - individual characters<sup>coming soon</sup>, everyone in a corporation or alliance<sup>coming soon</sup>,
    the whole Universe, or no one but you.</p>
    <p>Sharing can be stopped at anytime.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cover-try">
    <h2>Try it</h2>
    <% if signed_in? %>
      <%= link_to "Go to calendar", calendar_url %>
    <% else %>
      <%= eve_online_sso_button(:large) %>
      <p class="m-2"><%= link_to_eve_online_sso_help %></p>
    <% end %>
  </section>
</div>
